HOW TO AVOID FAKE AUCTION WEBSITES

Over the past few decades, the auction market has strived to achieve great credibility in the Brazilian market. With the arrival of Copart in Brazil in 2012, new technologies were implemented, yards across Brazil were opened and thousands of auctions have been held since.

Unfortunately, the auction market has been under constant attacks from criminals, and the biggest victim could be you: the Buyer.

Criminals have created fake auctions sites, often posing as real auctioneers in order to deceive consumers.

Donâ€™t run the risk of losing the investment of a lifetime, check below to see what the tips are for not falling into the scam of the fake auction websites.

Â 

IF SOMETHING SEEMS TOO GOOD TO BE TRUE, IT USUALLY IS

If the website is offering you a vehicle with an extremely low price compared to the market, you can be sure that it is a scam. Although auto auction prices are usually lower than the market price, we are not a charity. Be vigilant!

Â 

CHECK THE WEBSITEâ€™S ADDRESS

Another point to keep in mind, is to check the URL of the website you are accessing. In order to avoid being taken down, criminals host their websites outside of Brazil, and this is why we can identify the fake from the legitimate website.

Authetic auto auctions that occur within Brazil will always end with: .COM.BR

Fake websites, on the other hand, will always end up with variations like .COM/BR

Â 

CHECK YARDâ€™S ADDRESS

Criminals are experts at selling fake/non-existent vehicles. Therefore, always try to verify the address of the yard that is holding the auction. Another tip is to search the address on Google and make sure through the satellite images that there are vehicles in the indicated location. Take ample precaution and visit the yard if possible!

Check the location of all Copart Brazilâ€™s yard here: https://beta.copart.com.br/locations/

Â 

SALE WITHOUT AN AUCTION

Please note that all Copart Brazilâ€™s vehicles go to auction to be auctioned off to the highest bidder!

We will never sell a vehicle directly to a single buyer.

Â 

CHECK THE VEHICLEâ€™S PHOTOS

To certify the veracity of the lot for sale, pay attention to the photos of the vehicle, especially in two areas:

  • In Lot Display, at the bottom right corner of each vehicle picture, you will find Copartâ€™s logo together with the official website address (copart.com.br). Check out below:

Â 

  • Check the vehicle license plate, all of our lots have their photos captured with a Copart license plate cover. Check out below:

Â

PRIVATE INDIVIDUALS CANNOT NEGOTIATE IN COPARTâ€™S NAME

No private individual may sell a vehicle on behalf of Copart. If someone contacts you through WhatsApp or Facebook claiming to be a Copart employee and making an offer, donâ€™t trust it.

Our vehicles are only sold at face-to-face auctions that take place in a yard or through online auctions on our official website: beta.copart.com.br/ www.copart.com.br
